difference of these longitudes, and ascertain their positions then with
respect to the vernal and equinoctial points of intersection of the
equinoctial and ecliptic; according to the usual rate of the precession
of the equinoxes, one degree in seventy-one years and a half."\[1\]

A careful calculation, based on these principles, has proved that this
